BTracT

Banana Tracking Tool

BTracT is a system of integrated tools through API which consists of Musabase and Open data kit

In order to use BTracT, you need to

  1. Have an android mobile phone or tablet. Install,
    • ODK collect
    • ODK Sensors Framework
    • ODK printer driver (contact admin)

  2. Mobile printer (zebra zq520)

  3. User accounts in
    • Musabase test site or live site and
    • ONA (ODK aggregate server)

  4. Generate a crossing plan through Musabase

  5. Configure mobile phone with user accounts

  6. Collect data using mobile devices


1.0 Crossing plan

Crossing plan is generated with permissions through musabase.org

To create a crossing plan, go to manage menu >> select crosses


Click on Add Cross Wishlist (see highlight in the figure below)



1.1 Using specific field trial names

  1. Select your tool, specific to your site eg. BTracTTest in the Musabase test site


  1. Select the Female and Male trials. Select the specific accessions and assign priority. Click Next



1.2 Using lists


  1. First create your female and male lists

Next

  1. Select all female plots or specific plots in a block/field.

3.0 Data collection

BTracT get started

BTracT data collection tool is divided into three main sections

  1. Field Activities
    • Flowering
    • First pollination
    • Repeat pollination
    • Bunch harvesting
    • Seed extraction
    • Plant status


  1. Laboratory
    • Embryo culture
    • Embryo germination
    • Tissue culture
    • Rooting
    • Contamination


  1. Nursery
    • Potting
    • Hardening
    • Open field
